<entry>
<title type="text">Opera Skinning part 1: Introduction</title>
<link href="http://dev.opera.com/articles/view/opera-skinning" />
<author>
<name>Lars Kleinschmidt</name>
</author>
<content>In this series of articles, Opera skinning expert Lars Kleinschmidt provides the most complete analysis to date of the Opera skinning system. He first looks at the basics including how skins are packaged and how to make simple changes to your default skin, before going deep into how to customize every aspect of your Opera&#39;s look and feel by altering the graphics and contents of the skin.ini file. Every section of skin.ini is explored in detail. This series of articles is updated for Opera 9.5.</content>
<id>http://dev.opera.com/articles/view/opera-skinning</id>
